بث مباشر الفكرة منه زيادة الانتاجية والتحصيل بنظام ذاكر معي" أو 
"study with me" 
موعدنا يوميا إن شاء الله بعرفكم كمان قبلها و جدولنا ومواعيد المذاكرة هتنزل على قناة التلجيرام بإذن الله لذلك انضم 🔴
  📍OUR TELEGRAM CHANNEL:-https://t.me/mstudyfamg: 🚨 لقناة التليجرام 🌟 FOR STUDY TIMINGS & SCHEDULES ☝☝
   , كن معنا و اكسب مجتمع منجز و بيئة محفزة تعينك على ملل المذاكرة وجعلها ممتعة
 وده جروب التلجرام  أيضا اشترك فيه من هنا :📍https://t.me/mstudyfamhg🗓️ TELEGRAM GROUP
نعمل عليه تحديات و نتناقش في اي حاجع ممكن نعملها سواء كافكار للمذاكرة و المواعيد و مشاركات فعالة
اهلا بيك نورت العائلة💡, ( " وتعاونوا على البر و التقوى ولا تعاونوا على الْإِثْمِ والعدوان " ) نسعى الآية الكريمة بعون الله بجزئيها

1-نلتزم بحلية طالب العلم ووقاره 
2- اتقوا شر الاختلاط  و امنعوه  حرصا على تقوى الله في دينكم أنفسكم و أهلكم
3-نحترم قواعد البث و توقيره فهو مكان عيلتنا و اللي يعيننا على مذاكرتنا
 
جرب البومودورو معنا وراقب كيف ستزدهروتتحسن  نتائجك معنا
كن جزءًا من مجتمع يهدف إلى النجاح والتفوق، وتحقيق أعلى درجات الإنتاجية! 🚀
📍📚:-  https://t.me/mstudyfamg
📲 انضم الآن واستعد للتميز! 🔥

📌 تقنية البومودورو معانا هتساعدك تزود انتاجيتك بشكل ملحوظ لانك هتذاكر بمعدل 50 دقيقة و 10 دقائق راحة وبكده تكون
  قد استفدت افضل استفادة بالساعة التي تذاكرها بالاضافة الى وجودك معنا فستشعر بانك في عائلتك  مع الدراسة على اصوات المطر , قرآن , صوت الطبيعة و فواصل لطيفة تعينك على كسر ملل المذاكرة مليئة بالمرح و جو المسابقات لتستعيد نشاطك للاستمرار معنا الى الجلسة(السيشن) التالية وهكذا حتى ينتهي البث وتكون قد انجزت وتنتظر البث الجديد لتنتج اكثر واكثر , و يمكننا تعديل وقت البومودورو حسب اتفاقنا اثناء البث
                                                             *       *         *
وقت الدراسة :- ابتعد عن المشتت و يكون تركيزك التام على الدراسة فقط 
وقت الراحة :-تأخذ 10 دقائق للراجة او  للاسترخاء و التأمل , كما يمكنك القيام بتمارين بسيطة لتجديد نشاطك أو شرب مشروبك المفضل او حتى كوبا من الماء و الاستمتاع بالفاصل معنا عبر البث 
ثم تعود للجلسة التالية معنا بنشاط  جديد وسترى كيف تتحسن انتاجيتك و كفاءة مذاكرتك
 متنساش تشترك وتفعل الجرس عشان يوصلك الاشعار باللياف الجديد و تلحقه من اوله و بالتالي ترفع من انتاجيتك بشكل فعال و تحصل على اكبر عدد من ساعات الانجاز معا
                                                                     🚩  🚩   🚩


📌 Pomodoro technique with us will help you significantly increase your productivity because you will study for 50 minutes and 10 minutes of rest, and you will have made the best use of the hour that you study. In addition to being with us, you will feel like you are in your family while studying to the sounds of rain, the Qur’an, the sound of nature, and gentle breaks that help you take a break. The boredom of studying is full of fun and an atmosphere of competitions to regain your energy to continue with us until the next session, and so on until it ends. The stream has been completed and you are waiting for the new stream to produce more and more , We can modify the Pomodoro time according to our agreement during the stream 
                                                               *    *     *
"Study time: Stay away from distractions and be fully focused on studying only 
Rest time: You take 10 minutes to sit down or relax and meditate. You can also do simple exercises to renew your activity or drink your favorite drink or even a glass of water and enjoy the break with us via broadcast. 
Then come back to the next session with us with a new activity and you will see how your productivity and study efficiency will improve


LIKE. SHARE. SUBSCRIBE.❗️📚 :)

Be More Productive

📩open me:

Hi!
Welcome to another Study with me
Thanks for joining
_________________________

I hope this study video helps you avoid using social media while you study. You will find a quiet and cosy study room ambience in this video when studying at your home. Hopefully, this would get you motivated more for studying. You might hear the rain, birds, typing sounds and the flipping of pages (and cars too, unfortunately) from time to time, and I hope that helps you know that I'm there studying with you!

🔥Key to success - """"BE CONSISTENT""""🔥

___________________________

What are you studying and where are you joining from? I also wonder what type of videos you like, study at the library or study at home? Your opinions are quite important to me; and, if you let me know what type of videos you like to watch, I would be happy. 
_____________________________

✧･ﾟ at the beginning of the study sessions, make sure to:
- turn off anything you're not going to be using to study
- have your materials ready to go
- have drinks/food ready so you don't have to get up to go get necessities
- have a clear idea of what you want to accomplish during the session (i.e., choose a task from your to-do list)


✧･ﾟ during the breaks:
- stop working as soon as the timer hits, even if you're mid-sentence
- make sure to get up, do some simple stretches
- refill anything that needs to get refilled
- talk to friends/update family

✧･ﾟ at the end of this video:
if you want to continue studying, give yourself a longer break and you can the next session video!

you're set to go! ♡
_____________________________
💡Please adjust the volume for each of the background music that comes out.
The ASMR that comes out with 💡 is the sound of burning wood and Rain. 
_____________________________

We have a Chat bot- 🤖
Commands for chat bot- 

!hi - when you join in👋
!start - to start studying
!top - Top Points
!points -  to know your points💯
!complete - when done with the goal

Chat rules:
- Being nice and respectful is mandatory!
- Spamming, harassment, trolling, bullying, repeating and all capital messages are definitely prohibited!
- Please feel encouraged to write in English so no one would feel excluded in the chat :)
- Please check YouTube's Community Guidelines
_____________________________

To those who are starting :
In order to study or do anything for long periods of time you need a strong purpose and you must be willing to endure challenges. If I can do this, think about what you can accomplish. If you're starting out, start from low intervals(10-30 minutes) and gradually increase once you feel you're comfortable. If you feel like quitting, visualize your goals and evaluate your purpose. Learn to accept challenges in your life to become uncommon.

Escolha um ambiente tranquilo para estudar.

Faça anotações para revisar depois.

Se inscrever no canal e ativar o sininho 🔔 para futuras lives.

S57.description:
18 views  Streamed live on 3 Jan 2025
Study with me daily

Routine - FIRST SHIFT    6:00 AM to 11:00 AM

               SECOND SHIFT   12:30 PM to 5:30 AM
 
                                   (rest & gym)

               THIRD SHIFT            9:30 PM to 11:00 PM




hello friends (╯▽╰ )
i welcome you to another study session! let's be productive together for a few hours :))
u can read a lil study guide below!~~🌟

i filmed these during my finals season! i hope you enjoy them & can have a productive time here, and most importantly, enjoy the shots of ollie peacefully sleeping.
i tried to lower the volume of the loud sounds (i get in the zone and forget to be more careful handling materials) and cut around camera noises, however because of the length of the video, i always miss some and it makes me want to delete the video, never post it! but i'm curbing my perfectionism this year ≡(▔﹏▔)≡ & i promised a no music swm to viewers, so here it is. next one will be better, pinky promise. most of all, i just hope these can be a wonderful companion to those feeling less inspired to keep going.
i hope you have a wonderful weekend/week ahead of u 🥺 best of luck with all your studies!!~⭐ i hope you're healthy and strong. 
lots of love,
💗🐻
✧･ﾟ how it works: ✧･ﾟ
there are four study sessions
focus as best as you can during your study session because we'll be resting in just a bit. it will get easier the more you do it, as your brain can be trained to focus for longer periods of time as you study consistently, so don't give up! you can do this :-) 
aditionally, because this is a no music SWM, if you feel like it, you can always add your own playlists in the background or lofi streams, for example.

✧･ﾟ at the beginning of the study sessions, make sure to:
turn off anything you're not going to be using to study
have your materials ready to go
have drinks/food ready so you don't have to get up to go get necessities
have a clear idea of what you want to accomplish during the session (i.e., choose a task from your to-do list)

✧･ﾟ during the breaks:
stop working as soon as the timer hits, even if you're mid-sentence
make sure to get up, do some simple stretches
refill anything that needs to get refilled
talk to friends/update family

✧･ﾟ at the end of this video:
if you want to continue studying, give yourself a longer break and you can repeat this video!

you're set to go! ♡

(ꈍᴗꈍ) stay cozy!
